South Wiltshire UTC is a mixed University Technical College (UTC) located in Salisbury, Wiltshire, England. It opened in 2015 and caters for students aged 14â€“19 years.
The college specialises in science and engineering, and is backed by the University of Southampton. Its site on Wilton Road, about 1 mile (1.6 km) west of the centre of Salisbury, is a refurbished former police headquarters.
